 Sea, Vol. 2 -- tB Bibliographies -- t18 Bibliography I -- t19 Bibliography II -- t20 Bibliography III -- tAbout the Contributors -- tCORNELL EAST ASIA SERIES0 arestricted accessuhttp://purl.org/coar/access_right/c_16ecfonline access with authorization2star  aThe first book-length study of Wang Wenxing in English offering biographic, cultural, textual, literary, and linguistic readings of his work. The essays cover topics such as Wang's writing principles, typology of characters, analysis of lexicon, employment of stream-of-consciousness, musicality, relationship to Modernist writers of the West, relationship to Lu Xun, and issues of translating Wang's works into Western languages. Original contributions by Wang Wenxing illuminates his own writing through a discussion of his way of reading, and a biographical essay by Ch'en Chu-yun, his wife, who shares with the reader moments in their private life and the writing habits of her husband. In addition, this manuscript appends outlines of Wang's novels and bibliographies that are valuable to both students and scholars in their studies of Wang Wenxing's writing in particular as well as to the understanding of Taiwanese and Chinese literatures in general.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Feb 2023) 4aLiterary Studies. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / Asian / Chinese.2bisacsh1 aCai, Wei, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aChang, Sung-sheng Yvonne, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aChen, Jeannette Chu-yun, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDolling, Susan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aEdwards, Fred, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHung, San-hui, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 